ALICE M. McCOLLOUGH, v. THOMAS McCOLLOUGH 23 So. (2nd) 139

June Term, 1945

July 10, 1945 Division B Rehearing denied Sept. 10, 1945. Vincent C. Giblin and W. W. Colson, Jr., for appellant. Smathers, Thompson & Maxwell and John G. Thompson and L. ,S. Bonsteel, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

Upon appellant’s motion therefor it is ordered that the appellee, Thomas O. McCullough, pay to the appellant, Alice M. McCullough, within thirty days for the use of her counsel the sum of $417.40 to cover the following items: preparation of transcript, $296.40; verification and certification of the record, $46; and expenses of her counsel for arguiñg the matter in this court $75.

CHAPMAN, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
